<dl id="s14073as"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14073as">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s14all.htm#s14073as">sector 73(as)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> copper&apos;s nark</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>The Sign ofthe Lamp</i> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> She had scarce any friends, for she was known to be a <mark>copper&apos;s nark</mark>; thus came the fear in her step and the challenge in her eyes. <small> Thomas Burke, <a name="TBLN" href="/udra/udex.htm#tbln"><cite title="source">Limehouse Nights</cite></a> (1917), 135</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Nark: police informant. </mm> </dd></dl>
